title: Haiti: Betting on the Montana Accord
description: Georges Fauriol analyzes the Montana Accord and Haiti's fraught search for a sustainable political transition plan.

title: Thermal Imagery Analysis of Continued Activity at Yongbyon
description: LANDSAT 7 and LANDSAT 8 thermal infrared satellite imagery in January and February show that warm water is being discharged from the 5MWe reactor at Yongbyon, confirming that the reactor and its cooling system are in operation.

title: Data Protection or Data Utility?
description: While the United States is poised to enter a new period of productivity growth driven by the deployment of AI technologies, this data driven economic growth model raises serious concerns over individuals’ data privacy.

title: Russia’s Losing Hand in Ukraine
description: The United States and its partners and allies should be prepared to support Ukraine by exploiting Russian weaknesses and raising the financial and military costs of meddling in Ukraine, according to a new analysis by the CSIS Transnational Threats Project.

title: The Latest on Southeast Asia: February 17, 2022

description: As the world’s third-largest democracy, Indonesia is an important partner of the United States. The two sides are collaborating in ways that are not only bilateral, but increasingly regional and notably global.
